    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n6419" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νεμεσάω, νεμεσσάω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νέμεσις</span>), fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νεμεσήσω</span>, aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νεμέσησα</span>,
          mid. fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νεμεσήσομαι</span>, pass. aor. 3
          pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νεμέσσηθεν</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be
            indignant</span> or justly <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">angry</span> with one (at
          anything), <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινί</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τι</span>), <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">take it ill</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 6.286</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.494</span></i>; also
          w. part., or <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">οὕνεκα, φ 169</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 23.213</span></i>; mid., like active, also
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">shrink from, be ashamed</span>, w. inf., <i><span class="en">Od. 4.158</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
